        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 8:16PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 816 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northwest of Burlington to 6 miles
south of Union City to near Sturgis. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coldwater, Bronson, Quincy, Union City, Litchfield, Colon, Girard,
Batavia, Leonidas, Burr Oak, Sherwood, Fairfax, South Butler,
Findley, Matteson Lake, Marble Lake, and Hodunk.

This includes Interstate 69 in Michigan between mile markers 8 and
21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
